<span id="v.iii.xiii"></span>

<span id="v.iii.xiii-p1"></span> <span class="c1"><span
id="v.iii.xiii-p1.1"></span>Chapter XIII.—What Priests Should Be and
Should Not Be.</span>

<span id="v.iii.xiii-p2"></span>Beloved brethren! that a man should
build up and establish the brethren on the faith in one God, this also
is manifest and well-known.  This too, again, is comely, that a man
should not be envious of his neighbour.  And moreover, again, it is
suitable and comely that all those who work the works of the Lord should
work the works of the Lord in the fear of God.  Thus is it required of
them to conduct themselves.  That “the harvest is great, but the workmen
are few,” this also is well-known and manifest.  Let us, therefore, “ask
of the Lord of the harvest” that He would send forth workmen into the
harvest; <span id="fr_420"></span>[421](#fn_420.md) such workmen as “shall
skilfully dispense the word of truth;” workmen “who shall not be
ashamed;” <span id="fr_421"></span>[422](#fn_421.md) faithful workmen;
workmen who shall be “the light of the world;” <span
id="fr_422"></span>[423](#fn_422.md) workmen who “work not for the food
that perisheth, but for that food which abideth unto life
eternal;” <span id="fr_423"></span>[424](#fn_423.md) workmen who shall be
such as the apostles; workmen who imitate the Father, and the Son, and
the Holy Spirit; who are concerned for the salvation of men; not
“hireling” <span id="fr_424"></span>[425](#fn_424.md) workmen; not workmen
to whom the fear of God and righteousness appear to be gain; not workmen
who “serve their belly;” not workmen who “with fair speeches and
pleasant words mislead the hearts of the innocent;” <span
id="fr_425"></span>[426](#fn_425.md) not workmen who imitate the children
of light, while they are not light but darkness—“men whose end is
destruction;” <span id="fr_426"></span>[427](#fn_426.md) not workmen who
practise iniquity and wickedness and fraud; not “crafty workmen;” <span
id="fr_427"></span>[428](#fn_427.md) not workmen “drunken” and
“faithless;” <span id="fr_428"></span>[429](#fn_428.md) nor workmen who
traffic in Christ; <span id="fr_429"></span>[430](#fn_429.md) not
misleaders; not “lovers of money; not malevolent.” <span
id="fr_430"></span>[431](#fn_430.md)

<span id="v.iii.xiii-p14"></span>Let us, therefore, contemplate and
imitate the faithful who have conducted themselves well in the Lord, as
is becoming and suitable to our calling and profession.  Thus let us do
service before God in justice and righteousness, and without blemish,
“occupying ourselves with things good and comely before God *and* also
before men.” <span id="fr_431"></span>[432](#fn_431.md)   For this is
comely, that God be glorified in us in all things.

<span id="v.iii.xiii-p16"></span>*Here* endeth the first Epistle of
Clement.

